            "name": "Reuven Kimelman",
            "bio": "Rabbi Reuven Kimelman is a professor of Classical Judaica at Brandeis University and rabbi of Beth Abraham New England Sephardic Congregation of New England. His forthcoming book is <em>The Rhetoric of Jewish Prayer: A Historical and Literary Commentary on the Daily Prayer Book</em>. His other book is <em>The Mystical Meaning of ‘Lekhah Dodi’ and ‘Kabbalat Shabbat’</em>.",
